# CLAUDE.md Example — Project Rules for Claude Code

# Project Overview
This is a Next.js 14 + TypeScript monorepo managed with Turborepo.

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Next.js 14 (App Router), React 18, TypeScript 5.3
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v3 + shadcn/ui
- Backend: tRPC v11, Drizzle ORM, PostgreSQL
- Testing: Vitest (unit), Playwright (E2E)
- Package Manager: pnpm 9+

## Architecture Rules
- All shared code lives in `packages/` — never import from sibling apps directly
- Use Server Components by default; add "use client" only when interactivity is needed
- API routes use tRPC routers defined in `packages/api/src/routers/`
- Database schema changes require a migration file via `pnpm db:migrate`

## Coding Standards
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use Zod schemas for all external input validation
- Error handling: use Result<T, E> pattern instead of throwing exceptions
- File naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components
- Max file length: 300 lines — split into smaller modules if exceeded

## Git Conventions
- Branch naming: `feat/`, `fix/`, `chore/`, `docs/` prefixes
- Commit messages follow Conventional Commits
- PRs require at least one approval before merge
- Squash merge to main

## Testing Requirements
- New features must include unit tests (Vitest)
- Critical user flows need E2E tests (Playwright)
- Test files are co-located: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts`
- Run `pnpm test` before committing

## Security
- Never hardcode API keys or secrets — use environment variables
- All user inputs must be sanitized before database queries
- Authentication tokens expire after 24 hours

## Common Commands
```bash
pnpm dev          # Start all apps in development mode
pnpm build        # Build all packages and apps
pnpm test         # Run unit tests
pnpm test:e2e     # Run Playwright E2E tests
pnpm db:migrate   # Run pending database migrations
pnpm lint         # ESLint + Prettier check
```

## Directory Structure
```
apps/
  web/           # Main Next.js application
  admin/         # Admin dashboard
packages/
  api/           # tRPC API layer
  db/            # Drizzle ORM schema & migrations
  ui/            # Shared UI components (shadcn/ui)
  config/        # Shared configs (ESLint, TypeScript, Tailwind)
```

## MCP Servers
This project uses the following MCP servers:
- GitHub: For issue/PR management
- Figma: For design-to-code workflows
- Slack: For team notifications

## Important Context
- This project serves ~10k monthly active users
- Deploy target is Vercel (web) and Cloud Run (API)
- The `packages/db` schema is the source of truth for data models
